draw(A--(3,1)--B);

draw(A--C--D--cycle);
[/asy] \\
The sides of the right triangle with hypotenuse = $\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$ are $30^{\circ}$-$60^{\circ}$-$90^{\circ}$ right triangles. Thus, the shorter leg opposite of the $30^{\circ}$ angle = $\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\div2 = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}$. Since there are 8 sides of length $\frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}$. We have: \\
\[4(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{4})^2 = \frac{1}{2} \\
Area \ of \ right \ triangles = \frac{1}{2}(side \ length \ of \ right \ triangle \ times \ length \ of \ right \ triangle)
\] \\
Therefore, the total area of all $8$ timngles is $\boxed{1}$ and the whole is $1+\frac{1}{2}= \boxed{\frac{3}{2}}$.
<answer> The area of the octagon is $\frac{3}{2}$.

